{"type":"message","id":"a200fad2","parentId":"2d5a8e43","timestamp":"2026-03-24T01:10:02.497Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-23 21:10 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Add a Calendar Widget to the Mission Control React app at /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/\n\nThe backend calendar API is already running at http://localhost:3001/api/calendar (returns {ok: true, events: [{title, date, calendar, allDay}]}).\n\n**What to build:**\nCreate `src/components/CalendarWidget.tsx`:\n- Fetch from http://localhost:3001/api/calendar every 60 seconds\n- Show upcoming events in a frosted glass panel matching the existing iOS 26 aesthetic\n- Display: event title, date/time, calendar name as a colored badge\n- Group events by \"Today\", \"This Week\", \"Later\" sections\n- Highlight Family Calendar events in a special color (they're Bobby's personal events)\n- All-day events show just the date, timed events show the time\n- Clean, minimal Apple Calendar-inspired look\n- Loading skeleton while fetching\n- Empty state: \"No upcoming events\"\n\n**Replace `src/App.tsx` to include the CalendarWidget:**\n- Remove the AgentGrid from the main view (we're focusing on the calendar)\n- Keep the Header with Mission Control title + clock\n- Add the CalendarWidget as the main content\n- Also keep a small status bar showing gateway connection status\n- The AgentGrid can be hidden or moved to a secondary view\n\n**Styling:** Keep it consistent with the existing frosted glass aesthetic (backdrop-blur-xl, bg-white/5, border-white/10, rounded-2xl)\n\n**Run npm run build when done.**\n\nMake it look clean and premium — Apple Calendar inspired."}],"timestamp":1774314602495}}
